FBIS4-37139 "drnes117_j_94013" FBIS-NES-94-117 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Six Killed in Attacks, Japanese Trawler Hit in Aden Six Killed in Attacks, Japanese Trawler Hit in Aden LD1706105494 Kuwait Radio Kuwait in Arabic 1000 GMT 17 Jun 94 LD1706105494 Kuwait Radio Kuwait Arabic BFN [Excerpt] The northern forces this morning resumed their shelling of the city of Aden and the suburb of Dar Sa'd and fired a number of Katyusha rockets and artillery shells. Six people were killed and 15 others were injured in the attacks. Maritime sources in Aden have reported that a trawler flying the Japanese flag has been hit by a shell in the port of Aden and that fire has been raging aboard the ship until 1000 this morning Kuwaiti time. [passage omitted]
